children: In this final track off of Biggie’s classic debut album
, Biggie calls up Puff Daddy in the middle of the night to explain to him that he’s about to commit suicide.
In one long verse B.I.G. explains that he feels unloved and expresses guilt for all the crimes he’s committed, while Puff tries to talk him out of killing himself in the song’s ad-libs.
The telephone vocal effect used on Puffy’s mic, plus other key sound effects (gunshots, the phone and Big’s body falling to the floor) make the track cinematic and haunting.
Despite Puff’s pleas Big pulls the trigger and kills himself at the end of the track. Biggie’s fictional death at the end of the song, directly ties into his follow-up album
The conceptual track became even more significant after The Notorious B.I.G. was murdered on March 9, 1997.
